        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "DetermineToDateFromBillingPeriodAndWDNumber",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. It is designed to calculate a specific date, referred to as the \"To Date,\" based on a given billing period and a workday number. This function is typically used in scenarios where billing cycles and workday calculations are essential, such as financial reporting or payroll processing."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
